data.enText: an amount of sth that is provided or available to be used
The water supply is unsafe.
Supplies of food are almost exhausted.

data.chText: 我们不能保证提供充足的原料。
data.enText: We cannot guarantee adequate supplies of raw materials.
Books were in short supply (= there were not enough of them) .

data.chText: （军队或探险队等的）补给，补给品
data.enText: the things such as food, medicines, fuel, etc. that are needed by a group of people, for example an army or expedition
Our supplies were running out.

data.chText: 一架为难民运送食物和医疗用品的运输机
data.enText: a transport plane carrying food and medical supplies for refugees
the act of supplying sth

data.chText: 联合国已同意允许提供紧急援助。
data.enText: The UN has agreed to allow the supply of emergency aid.

data.chText: 中风可导致大脑供氧中断。
data.enText: A stroke can disrupt the supply of oxygen to the brain.
The electricity supply (= the system supplying electricity) had been cut off.
supplies
supplying
supplied
supplied
to provide sb/sth with sth that they need or want, especially in large quantities

data.chText: 一些外国政府向反叛者提供武器。
data.enText: Foreign governments supplied arms to the rebels.

data.chText: 一些外国政府向反叛者提供武器。
data.enText: Foreign governments supplied the rebels with arms.

data.chText: 许多志愿者来自当地学校。
data.enText: Local schools supply many of the volunteers.

data.chText: 为我们提供日常所需维生素的食物
data.enText: foods supplying our daily vitamin needs

ex.enText: The manager offered him a cigarette.

ex.chText: 他给她提供了一份好工作，但她拒绝了。
ex.enText: He offered her a good job, but she turned it down.

synonyms.bx: 指主动给予帮助等，对方可以接受也可以拒绝。

ex.chText: 这房间可以看到迷人的海景。
ex.enText: The room affords a fascinating sea view.

ex.chText: 这给了他与外国的同龄人交流的机会。
ex.enText: It afforded him the opportunity to communicate with his foreign peers.

synonyms.bx: 多指提供抽象的东西，可后接双宾语。

ex.chText: 这些新的发现是否会提供更多与案件有关的线索？
ex.enText: Will these new finds furnish more clues surrounding the case?

ex.chText: 他得到了一份当地经销商的名单。
ex.enText: He was furnished with a list of local dealers.

synonyms.bx: 既可指提供抽象的东西，又可指提供具体的东西。

ex.chText: 这家餐厅为客人提供免费甜点。
ex.enText: The restaurant provides free desserts for guests.

ex.chText: 他们已给我提供了所需要的一切。
ex.enText: They have already provided me with everything I need.

ex.chText: 孩子们有良好的衣食供应。
ex.enText: The kids are provided with good food and clothing.

ex.chText: 当局有义务为老年人提供住所。
ex.enText: It is the duty of the authorities to provide homes for the old.

synonyms.bx: 指为某人提供需要或有用的东西，多用于 provide sth for sb 和provide sb with sth 结构中。

ex.chText: 这个项目所用的钢材由一家国际公司提供。
ex.enText: Steel for this project was supplied by an international company.

ex.chText: 他们因为向街头小贩提供假药而被捕。
ex.enText: They were arrested for supplying counterfeit medicine to street vendors.

ex.chText: 我们给附近的5个城镇提供电力。
ex.enText: We supply power to the five nearby towns.

synonyms.bx: 尤指长时间地定期供应所需或想要之物，多用于 supply sb with sth 和 supply sth to sb 结构中。

tr: the activity of supplying or providing something
offering goods and services for sale
an amount of something available for use
give what is desired or needed, especially support, food or sustenance
example: The hostess provided lunch for all the guests

tr: give something useful or necessary to
example: We provided the room with an electrical heater

tr: circulate or distribute or equip with
example: issue a new uniform to the children

value.def: If you supply someone with something that they want or need, you give them a quantity of it.

example.ex: ...an agreement not to produce or supply chemical weapons.
example.tran: 不生产或供应化学武器的协议

example.ex: ...a pipeline which will supply the major Greek cities with Russian natural gas.
example.tran: 从俄罗斯向希腊主要城市输送天然气的管道

example.ex: ...the blood vessels supplying oxygen to the brain.

value.def: You can use supplies to refer to food, equipment, and other essential things that people need, especially when these are provided in large quantities.

example.ex: What happens when food and gasoline supplies run low?...
example.tran: 如果食物和汽油供应减少，会出现什么情况呢？

example.ex: The country's only supplies are those it can import by lorry from Vietnam.
example.tran: 这个国家仅有的补给品是用卡车从越南进口来的。

value.tran: (尤指大量的)补给，补给品，日用物资

value.def: A supply of something is an amount of it which someone has or which is available for them to use.

example.ex: The brain requires a constant supply of oxygen...
Most urban water supplies in the United States now contain fluoride in varying amounts.
example.tran: 现在美国大部分城市供水中都存在含量不一的氟化物。

value.def: Supply is the quantity of goods and services that can be made available for people to buy.

example.ex: Prices change according to supply and demand.
example.tran: 价格受供求关系的影响。

value.def: If you supply a missing word or piece of information, for example in a puzzle, you say or write it because you know it.

example.ex: Supply the missing word(s) and you could win a T-shirt.
example.tran: 填出所缺少的单词，你就会赢得一件T恤。

value.def: If something is in short supply, there is very little of it available and it is difficult to find or obtain.

example.ex: Food is in short supply all over the country...
example.tran: 全国普遍食品供应不足。

example.ex: Nowadays that sort of innocence is in short supply.
example.tran: 现在那种天真烂漫很少见。
